\description{
\code{sus_grid_pollution_merra2()} downloads, spatially aggregates, and caches
NASA MERRA-2 aerosol and air quality data for Brazilian municipalities.

MERRA-2 (Modern-Era Retrospective Analysis for Research and Applications v2)
from NASA GMAO provides global atmospheric reanalysis from \strong{1980 to
present} at 0.625\eqn{\times}0.5\eqn{^\circ} (~55 km). It is the longest
available reanalysis record for aerosol and pollution studies, making it
ideal for historical trend analysis and cross-validation with higher-
resolution products such as CAMS or GHAP.

Supported variables:
\itemize{
\item \strong{PM2.5} (\code{"pm25"}) — derived from aerosol mass components
(\eqn{\mu g/m^3}): \code{DUSMASS25 + SSSMASS25 + BCSMASS + 1.4*OCSMASS + SO4SMASS}, each multiplied by 1\eqn{\times}10^9 to convert kg/m\eqn{^3}
to \eqn{\mu g/m^3}.
\item \strong{AOD} (\code{"aod"}) — Total aerosol optical depth at 550 nm
(\code{TOTEXTTAU}), dimensionless, proxy for total aerosol column.
\item \strong{SO2} (\code{"so2"}, experimental) — sulfate surface mass concentration
from M2I3NVAER (\eqn{\mu g/m^3}).
}
}
